abstract: Corrupt forces find it easy to manipulate this president.
snippet: Corrupt forces find it easy to manipulate this president.
lead_paragraph: Kenneth McCallion is a New York lawyer who once represented former Prime Minister Yulia Tymoshenko of Ukraine. A few years ago, he brought a civil racketeering lawsuit on her behalf against some now familiar figures like Paul Manafort and the Ukrainian oligarch Dmitry Firtash. He knows a lot about corruption in Ukraine, and he said that earlier this year F.B.I. counterintelligence investigators approached him for information about Rudy Giuliani’s Ukrainian activities.

snippet: House Democrats released the first two transcripts of their closed-door impeachment testimonies.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The House committees leading the impeachment inquiry on Monday moved to open their proceedings to the public, releasing the first two transcripts of hours of testimony they have taken behind closed doors.

abstract: And without reform, neither is a Democratic Senate.
snippet: And without reform, neither is a Democratic Senate.
lead_paragraph: There are still more than a dozen candidates jockeying for the Democratic presidential nomination. Some are running on big, ambitious platforms for change, like the Medicare-for-All plans pushed by Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren. Others are selling “pragmatism,” with more modest ideas meant to win consensus — and which are often quite liberal by historical standards. But nearly everyone on the board faces the same, fundamental problem: They want to go further than where Congress, and the Senate in particular, will want to move, even if it has a Democratic majority.

abstract: She has led the way, but all the candidates need to come clean about their health care proposals.
snippet: She has led the way, but all the candidates need to come clean about their health care proposals.
lead_paragraph: Laying the table for the next Democratic debate, Elizabeth Warren has issued a plan that explains how she would fund what she calls Medicare for All. She had studiously avoided saying whether it would raise taxes for the middle class, and in her proposal, she says (repeatedly) it will not.

headline_main: Donald Trump, George Soros and Your Local Elections

abstract: Signs that the president’s advantage in the Electoral College has persisted or even increased since 2016.
snippet: Signs that the president’s advantage in the Electoral College has persisted or even increased since 2016.
lead_paragraph: Despite low national approval ratings and the specter of impeachment, President Trump remains highly competitive in the battleground states likeliest to decide his re-election, according to a set of new surveys from The New York Times Upshot and Siena College.

abstract: Gary Locke, a former governor of Washington, is trying to persuade fellow Asian-Americans to support Referendum 88,  which would restore affirmative action.

lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — As he stood before a bustling ballroom at a Chinese restaurant on Lake Union in September, Washington State’s former governor Gary Locke began by acknowledging the tension in the crowd.

abstract: Former President Petro Poroshenko alternately flattered President Trump, signed deals with U.S. firms and met with Rudolph Giuliani.
snippet: Former President Petro Poroshenko alternately flattered President Trump, signed deals with U.S. firms and met with Rudolph Giuliani.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Long before a telephone call with Ukraine’s president that prompted an impeachment inquiry, President Trump was exchanging political favors with a different Ukrainian leader, who desperately sought American help for his country’s struggle against Russian aggression.
